00:07:03.856 --> 00:07:06.259 line:95%,end
JILL: Ooh!

00:07:06.526 --> 00:07:11.431 line:95%,end
Your buddy, Chloe,
will portray Marilyn Monroe.

00:07:11.497 --> 00:07:13.332 line:95%,end
No! That's not fair!

00:07:15.201 --> 00:07:19.372 line:95%,end
And Maddie,
who else is there but Princess
Di?

00:07:19.439 --> 00:07:20.840 line:95%,end
Ooh, I love her.

00:07:21.674 --> 00:07:23.309 line:95%,end
ABBY LEE: All right. You can go.

00:07:23.376 --> 00:07:24.510 line:95%,end
Girls, spread apart.

00:07:24.577 --> 00:07:26.879 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:07:30.616 --> 00:07:31.617 line:5%,start
Let's go from the top.

00:07:31.684 --> 00:07:33.352 line:5%,start
Let's see what we have.
Let's all dance it. Hit it!

00:07:33.419 --> 00:07:34.654 line:5%,start
I hear echoes inside myself.

00:07:34.720 --> 00:07:35.721 line:95%,end
ABBY LEE: Come on, push.

00:07:35.788 --> 00:07:37.924 line:95%,end
Get in the ball of that foot,
right off the floor.

00:07:37.990 --> 00:07:40.393 line:95%,end
One, two, three, four, five.

00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:42.528 line:95%,end
Yay! Good girl!

00:07:42.595 --> 00:07:46.432 line:95%,end
This week, the routine
is entitled Gone Too Soon.

00:07:47.066 --> 00:07:49.235 line:95%,end
This is a contemporary routine.

00:07:49.302 --> 00:07:54.273 line:95%,end
It has very intricate timing,
and it's also characterization.

00:07:54.340 --> 00:07:57.710 line:95%,end
These girls need to become one
with their character.

00:07:57.777 --> 00:08:00.613 line:95%,end
And they better bring it on,
because everybody


00:08:00.680 --> 00:08:02.949 line:95%,end
in that audience,
including the judges,

00:08:03.015 --> 00:08:05.585 line:95%,end
needs to easily recognize
their character.

00:08:05.651 --> 00:08:07.386 line:95%,end
I got to let you go
in a few minutes.

00:08:07.453 --> 00:08:08.921 line:95%,end
I want to not keep
choreographing.

00:08:08.988 --> 00:08:09.989 line:95%,end
I want to go over the story.

00:08:10.056 --> 00:08:13.693 line:95%,end
You need to tell the audience
and the judges

00:08:13.759 --> 00:08:16.362 line:95%,end
they shouldn't know
who you are because of the
costume.

00:08:16.429 --> 00:08:17.797 line:95%,end
They should know
who you are

00:08:17.864 --> 00:08:19.332 line:95%,end
because you're
telling the story.

00:08:19.398 --> 00:08:20.399 line:95%,end
Do your homework.

00:08:20.466 --> 00:08:22.969 line:95%,end
Look on the internet, Google it.
Figure it out.

00:08:23.035 --> 00:08:26.272 line:95%,end
Or maybe just one of you will be
gone too soon

00:08:26.339 --> 00:08:27.607 line:95%,end
from the Abby Lee Dance Company.

00:08:28.808 --> 00:08:30.343 line:95%,end
KELLY: But what shall
we have Abby be?

