doing a hip-hop dance, beat you.

00:17:37.523 --> 00:17:38.524 line:95%,end
Really?

00:17:38.590 --> 00:17:40.459 line:95%,end
Maddie is doing a tap solo.

00:17:40.526 --> 00:17:41.827 line:95%,end
I am thrilled.

00:17:42.327 --> 00:17:44.830 line:95%,end
She's a great tapper,
it's a cute little number.

00:17:44.897 --> 00:17:46.965 line:95%,end
It's called Me and
You Against the World.

00:17:47.299 --> 00:17:49.902 line:95%,end
And it's all about
a housewife that woke up

00:17:49.968 --> 00:17:51.236 line:95%,end
on the wrong side of the bed.

00:17:51.303 --> 00:17:53.772 line:95%,end
She burnt the bacon
and the pancakes.

00:17:53.839 --> 00:17:55.774 line:95%,end
She spilled coffee
on her husband.

00:17:55.841 --> 00:17:57.109 line:95%,end
I mean, the whole nine yards.

00:17:57.176 --> 00:17:58.343 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:17:58.410 --> 00:17:59.978 line:95%,end
I hope you understand.

00:18:00.412 --> 00:18:03.816 line:95%,end
Call me up after
a bad day of work.

00:18:04.716 --> 00:18:05.784 line:5%,start
MADDIE: I love tapping.

00:18:05.851 --> 00:18:08.554 line:5%,start
I've always been tapping
ever since I was four.

00:18:08.620 --> 00:18:10.122 line:95%,end
It's one of my best strengths.

00:18:12.157 --> 00:18:13.459 line:95%,end
That's a good song.

00:18:13.525 --> 00:18:14.960 line:95%,end
Yeah, it's a great solo.
HOLLY: Yeah, it really is.

00:18:15.027 --> 00:18:16.428 line:95%,end
I like the music.

00:18:17.196 --> 00:18:19.765 line:95%,end
I thought Abby said she
wasn't running Maddie's solo.

00:18:19.832 --> 00:18:21.633 line:95%,end
She did.
She told me that today when I
walked in.

00:18:23.068 --> 00:18:24.269 line:95%,end
That's what she told me.

00:18:24.336 --> 00:18:26.405 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: I'm thinking she's
going to keep her promise

00:18:26.472 --> 00:18:27.806 line:95%,end
about not running Chloe's.

00:18:27.873 --> 00:18:29.508 line:95%,end
- KELLY: [laughs]
- Something just tells me maybe.

00:18:29.575 --> 00:18:30.676 line:95%,end
That promise she
might keep, but I'm--

00:18:30.742 --> 00:18:32.511 line:95%,end
Melissa's not
Chloe's mother so--

00:18:32.744 --> 00:18:34.613 line:95%,end
Of course, Chloe's not
working on her solo.

00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:36.081 line:95%,end
This is the way it goes here.

00:18:36.148 --> 00:18:38.150 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:18:43.322 --> 00:18:44.990 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:18:45.057 --> 00:18:47.359 line:95%,end
Abby, she make sure
that nobody wins.

00:18:47.426 --> 00:18:48.760 line:95%,end
And when Chloe did
win, she made sure

00:18:48.827 --> 00:18:51.196 line:95%,end
that she went to the judges
and fixed their mistake.

00:18:51.263 --> 00:18:56.268 line:95%,end
This score ended up
being 97.5, 97 and 1/2.

00:18:56.668 --> 00:19:02.441 line:95%,end
This should be 96.6.

00:19:03.041 --> 00:19:04.042 line:5%,start
This is your winner.

00:19:05.244 --> 00:19:06.645 line:95%,end
ABBY LEE: Maddie won everything.

00:19:07.779 --> 00:19:09.348 line:95%,end
Melissa, Christi said,
when she came in,

00:19:09.414 --> 00:19:10.749 line:95%,end
you were having a
meeting with Abby.

00:19:10.816 --> 00:19:11.950 line:95%,end
What were you
talking to her about?

00:19:12.017 --> 00:19:13.018 line:95%,end
I wasn't having a meeting.

00:19:13.085 --> 00:19:14.253 line:95%,end
I was talking to her.

00:19:14.319 --> 00:19:15.487 line:95%,end
What about?

00:19:15.554 --> 00:19:16.622 line:95%,end
None of your concern.

00:19:22.628 --> 00:19:24.062 line:95%,end
Not that you care,
because you hate my kids.

00:19:24.129 --> 00:19:26.064 line:95%,end
- So don't worry about it.
- Who said I hate your kids?

00:19:26.131 --> 00:19:27.332 line:95%,end
MELISSA: It's none
of your concern.

00:19:27.399 --> 00:19:29.568 line:95%,end
My kids are not your concern,
so don't worry about them.

00:19:30.869 --> 00:19:32.504 line:95%,end
KELLY: We all told
you though, Melissa--

00:19:32.571 --> 00:19:33.572 line:95%,end
I don't-- I don't--

00:19:33.639 --> 00:19:34.640 line:95%,end
I don't need to hear anything.

00:19:34.706 --> 00:19:36.575 line:95%,end
- But whenever--
- MELISSA: I don't need to hear.

00:19:36.642 --> 00:19:37.676 line:95%,end
- Whenever--
- I really don't.

00:19:37.743 --> 00:19:38.744 line:95%,end
JILL: --we talk to
you about this--

00:19:38.810 --> 00:19:39.811 line:95%,end
- I don't care.
- JILL: --you said--

00:19:39.878 --> 00:19:41.680 line:95%,end
I don't care. I'm over it.

00:19:41.747 --> 00:19:45.384 line:95%,end
Okay. But then you can't be mad
at us for something you chose to
do.

00:19:45.450 --> 00:19:47.819 line:95%,end
For talking about my husband,
it has nothing to do with my
kids.

00:19:47.886 --> 00:19:49.821 line:95%,end
JILL: No, I'm not talking
about your husband.

00:19:49.888 --> 00:19:50.989 line:95%,end
Oh, bull crap.

00:19:51.056 --> 00:19:52.591 line:95%,end
I never said anything
about your husband.

00:19:54.159 --> 00:19:55.194 line:95%,end
What did I say
about your husband?

00:19:55.260 --> 00:19:56.595 line:95%,end
Nothing. I don't want
to talk about it.

00:19:56.662 --> 00:19:58.297 line:95%,end
But I want to know why you
don't think we should say

00:19:58.363 --> 00:19:59.798 line:95%,end
something to you when--
- I don't care.

00:19:59.865 --> 00:20:01.333 line:95%,end
- You already said something.
- JILL: --it was affecting our
kids.

00:20:01.400 --> 00:20:03.001 line:95%,end
Whatever.

00:20:03.068 --> 00:20:06.171 line:95%,end
JILL: We just want you to
live up to what you do.

00:20:06.238 --> 00:20:07.372 line:95%,end
I told you what I was doing.

00:20:07.439 --> 00:20:08.540 line:95%,end
And I'm done with it.
- No, you didn't.

00:20:08.607 --> 00:20:10.175 line:95%,end
- MELISSA: I'm done talking.
- We called you and asked you
about it.

00:20:10.242 --> 00:20:11.410 line:95%,end
My kids, they come first.

00:20:11.710 --> 00:20:13.645 line:95%,end
And I'm fine, I
can handle my kids.

00:20:13.712 --> 00:20:14.880 line:95%,end
I can take care of my kids.

00:20:14.947 --> 00:20:16.448 line:95%,end
That's what we're
doing with our kids.

00:20:16.515 --> 00:20:18.016 line:95%,end
- We're trying to protect them.
- Then protect them.

00:20:18.083 --> 00:20:19.651 line:95%,end
- JILL: Because--
- MELISSA: That's your job.

00:20:19.718 --> 00:20:22.421 line:95%,end
--you went against
us and hurt them.

00:20:22.821 --> 00:20:24.089 line:95%,end
I did not hurt your kids.

00:20:24.456 --> 00:20:25.724 line:95%,end
- Yes, you did.
- Okay, whatever.

00:20:25.791 --> 00:20:27.192 line:95%,end
I hurt your kids.
I'm a bad person.

00:20:27.559 --> 00:20:28.927 line:95%,end
Kill me.

00:20:29.795 --> 00:20:31.763 line:95%,end
I'm sure you wish I would die
in a car accident too.

00:20:31.830 --> 00:20:33.732 line:95%,end
HOLLY: Oh, no, Melissa.
Oh, my god.


00:20:37.369 --> 00:20:38.770 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: Shall we
belly up to the bar?

00:20:38.837 --> 00:20:39.905 line:5%,start
Let's do it.

00:20:39.972 --> 00:20:42.507 line:5%,start
I love when the moms finally
break free of dance jail.

00:20:42.574 --> 00:20:44.643 line:5%,start
You know, we get to hang out,
we get to have drinks,

00:20:44.710 --> 00:20:45.811 line:95%,end
you know, vent a little bit.

00:20:45.877 --> 00:20:47.346 line:95%,end
- I'll have a diet cola.
- WOMAN: Sure.

00:20:47.412 --> 00:20:49.114 line:95%,end
Shoot, I was going to get that.

00:20:49.181 --> 00:20:50.415 line:95%,end
She lives on the edge.

00:20:50.482 --> 00:20:52.517 line:95%,end
I'll have the $100 martini.

00:20:52.951 --> 00:20:54.653 line:95%,end
Is anyone really missing
from the picture?

00:20:55.654 --> 00:20:56.822 line:95%,end
No. We're all here.

00:20:56.888 --> 00:20:58.857 line:95%,end
I could not believe
earlier that Melissa

00:20:58.924 --> 00:21:01.793 line:95%,end
said that we hope her
and her kids died in a car
crash.

00:21:01.860 --> 00:21:02.861 line:95%,end
Yeah, I hate that.

00:21:02.928 --> 00:21:04.396 line:95%,end
I hate, hate, hate that--
HOLLY: That was just crazy.

00:21:04.463 --> 00:21:05.464 line:95%,end
That's crazy.

00:21:05.530 --> 00:21:06.865 line:95%,end
If she really believes
that, then we're in trouble.

00:21:06.932 --> 00:21:08.200 line:95%,end
- Who thinks that way?
- I don't know.

00:21:08.267 --> 00:21:09.301 line:95%,end
That was crazy.

00:21:09.368 --> 00:21:10.602 line:95%,end
I mean, if that's
the way she feels,

00:21:10.702 --> 00:21:12.170 line:95%,end
you know, I don't
want to be her friend.

00:21:12.237 --> 00:21:13.639 line:95%,end
Melissa sat there
and told all of us--

00:21:13.739 --> 00:21:15.474 line:95%,end
- She wouldn't go.
- CHRISTI: She promised.

00:21:15.540 --> 00:21:16.608 line:95%,end
What does that make you think?

00:21:16.675 --> 00:21:18.076 line:95%,end
Because that makes me think
that she doesn't really

00:21:18.143 --> 00:21:19.144 line:95%,end
value our friendship.

00:21:19.211 --> 00:21:20.912 line:95%,end
She's definitely made
it out that dance

00:21:20.979 --> 00:21:22.481 line:95%,end
is more important than school.

00:21:22.547 --> 00:21:24.816 line:95%,end
If the only thing that's
important to you in life

00:21:24.883 --> 00:21:27.552 line:95%,end
is getting your kids ahead
of other people in dance,

00:21:27.819 --> 00:21:30.656 line:95%,end
don't sit upstairs
and pretend you don't care.

00:21:31.056 --> 00:21:34.559 line:95%,end
If your kids win or
lose, own who you are.

00:21:34.626 --> 00:21:36.895 line:95%,end
- Yeah.
- Stop lying to our faces.

00:21:36.962 --> 00:21:40.666 line:95%,end
Maddie had an hour with Abby,
Mackenzie had two hours with
Abby,

00:21:40.732 --> 00:21:42.100 line:95%,end
and Chloe got none?

00:21:42.167 --> 00:21:45.003 line:95%,end
If you can't see that's wrong,
then you are really blind.

00:21:45.070 --> 00:21:46.138 line:95%,end
You have a problem.

00:21:46.204 --> 00:21:48.840 line:5%,start
The fundamental
issue is your word.

00:21:48.940 --> 00:21:51.677 line:5%,start
You know, friendship,
what is it worth?

00:21:52.144 --> 00:21:55.947 line:95%,end
And what has taught me
was that I can't trust everybody

00:21:56.048 --> 00:21:57.482 line:5%,start
when they give their word.

00:21:59.184 --> 00:22:01.353 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:22:01.420 --> 00:22:02.487 line:5%,start
ABBY LEE: Guys, come on.

00:22:02.554 --> 00:22:04.289 line:5%,start
We're getting on a bus,
we're going tomorrow.

00:22:04.389 --> 00:22:08.894 line:5%,start
This is the first competition
we've been back since I was
gone.

00:22:09.528 --> 00:22:13.298 line:5%,start
The group number
is fine choreographically.

00:22:13.365 --> 00:22:18.503 line:95%,end
But I don't see that skill
of characterization shining
through.

00:22:18.570 --> 00:22:20.472 line:95%,end
And your competition
except exit.

00:22:20.539 --> 00:22:22.074 line:95%,end
That was a hot mess.

00:22:22.708 --> 00:22:23.875 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: I don't
like sitting up here.

00:22:23.942 --> 00:22:25.977 line:95%,end
I like sitting at
the bar last night.

00:22:26.078 --> 00:22:28.480 line:95%,end
- The bar last night.
- That was way more fun than
this.

00:22:28.547 --> 00:22:29.948 line:95%,end
KELLY: That was way better.

00:22:30.515 --> 00:22:32.117 line:95%,end
You should have came
with us last night.

00:22:32.584 --> 00:22:35.020 line:95%,end
I went home with my
husband and kids.

00:22:35.954 --> 00:22:38.357 line:5%,start
I couldn't care less if the moms
went out to drink without me.

00:22:38.457 --> 00:22:39.891 line:5%,start
I'm not much of a drinker.

00:22:39.958 --> 00:22:42.828 line:95%,end
So I'd rather be home with
my kids and my husband.

00:22:42.894 --> 00:22:45.197 line:95%,end
We all talked about it.
Jill was supposed to ask you.

00:22:45.263 --> 00:22:47.833 line:95%,end
- I was?
- Mackenzie wasn't feeling well.

00:22:47.899 --> 00:22:52.104 line:5%,start
I didn't realize it was
my job to invite Melissa.

00:22:57.175 --> 00:22:58.210 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:22:58.276 --> 00:23:01.046 line:95%,end
Banging the walls for help.

00:23:01.146 --> 00:23:02.748 line:95%,end
Some kind of malady--

00:23:02.814 --> 00:23:05.484 line:95%,end
Chloe, you need to make sure
you're that way a little bit
more.

00:23:05.917 --> 00:23:08.153 line:95%,end
Point your feet, Paige,
in the middle of the stage.

00:23:08.220 --> 00:23:09.921 line:95%,end
Foot underneath you.
Foot underneath you.

00:23:09.988 --> 00:23:14.493 line:95%,end
Some of the kids are still
trying to remember what step
comes next.

00:23:14.559 --> 00:23:15.627 line:95%,end
Come on, kiddos.

00:23:15.694 --> 00:23:17.963 line:95%,end
You have been doing
this for three years.


00:23:19.331 --> 00:23:21.299 line:5%,start
[suspenseful music]

00:23:22.634 --> 00:23:23.635 line:5%,start
Hey, ladies.

00:23:23.702 --> 00:23:24.936 line:5%,start
JILL: Hello.
- Hey!

00:23:25.003 --> 00:23:26.405 line:95%,end
- How are you?
- I'm good.

00:23:26.471 --> 00:23:28.206 line:95%,end
- How are you?
- HOLLY: I'm hanging in there.

00:23:28.573 --> 00:23:30.876 line:95%,end
Christi, by the way,
Payton's going to stay 15
minutes late

00:23:30.942 --> 00:23:32.477 line:95%,end
and help Chloe with her solo.

00:23:33.478 --> 00:23:36.348 line:95%,end
Did Leslie just rear
her ugly head again?

00:23:36.782 --> 00:23:39.184 line:95%,end
I thought we got rid of her.
Why is she back?

00:23:39.251 --> 00:23:41.453 line:95%,end
You're sitting here
listening to this woman,

00:23:41.520 --> 00:23:43.655 line:95%,end
this drunk, say
what she's saying.

00:23:43.722 --> 00:23:45.190 line:95%,end
- And you're sitting here--
- Call me a drunk again.

00:23:45.957 --> 00:23:48.794 line:95%,end
You're not just sitting here
and not telling us what you

00:23:48.894 --> 00:23:50.862 line:95%,end
really-- like you
are okay with it.

00:23:50.929 --> 00:23:53.432 line:95%,end
So when we leave, you're not
going to complain to Abby.

00:23:53.498 --> 00:23:55.967 line:95%,end
If Abby asks Payton
to dance with your kids,

00:23:56.067 --> 00:23:59.237 line:95%,end
then I'm fine with it.
We are in it 100%.

00:24:00.038 --> 00:24:01.640 line:95%,end
Anyway, we'll see
you around, ladies.

00:24:01.740 --> 00:24:03.442 line:95%,end
All right, bye.

00:24:04.109 --> 00:24:05.343 line:95%,end
Leslie's back.

00:24:05.410 --> 00:24:07.312 line:95%,end
I think that she's
been planning on trying

00:24:07.379 --> 00:24:08.880 line:95%,end
to get her daughter in with
this team since day one.

00:24:08.947 --> 00:24:10.482 line:95%,end
Oh, I do think that's her plan.

00:24:10.549 --> 00:24:14.653 line:95%,end
It's not often that people
come up here just to say hello

00:24:14.719 --> 00:24:15.921 line:95%,end
and be nice.

00:24:17.055 --> 00:24:18.356 line:95%,end
She likes to stir the pot.

00:24:18.423 --> 00:24:20.292 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: I have enough
crazy dance moms

00:24:20.358 --> 00:24:21.526 line:95%,end
to deal with sitting upstairs.

00:24:21.593 --> 00:24:23.862 line:95%,end
I don't need to engage with
two women who are clearly here

00:24:23.929 --> 00:24:24.963 line:95%,end
just to pick a fight.

00:24:25.030 --> 00:24:26.998 line:95%,end
We're all stocked
up on crazy here.

00:24:27.065 --> 00:24:30.669 line:95%,end
KELLY: Did you think at all,
Melissa, about what we talked
about?

00:24:30.735 --> 00:24:32.871 line:95%,end
You understand where
we're coming from?

00:24:32.938 --> 00:24:36.675 line:95%,end
I got upset when you talk
about my personal business,
because it's--

00:24:36.741 --> 00:24:38.276 line:95%,end
I didn't talk about
your personal business.

00:24:38.343 --> 00:24:39.811 line:95%,end
It's none of anybody's concern.

00:24:39.878 --> 00:24:42.380 line:95%,end
But you sat here and you said,
oh, you guys hate me.

00:24:42.447 --> 00:24:45.150 line:95%,end
- You hate my kids.
- I don't-- I never said--

00:24:45.217 --> 00:24:47.953 line:95%,end
I never said you guys
hate me and my kids.

00:24:48.019 --> 00:24:49.988 line:95%,end
I know you don't like my kids,
and that's fine.

00:24:50.055 --> 00:24:51.122 line:95%,end
But that's not true.

00:24:51.189 --> 00:24:53.625 line:95%,end
What we're trying to say to you,
Melissa, is none of this

00:24:53.692 --> 00:24:55.794 line:95%,end
has anything to do with
Maddie or Mackenzie.

00:24:55.861 --> 00:24:57.529 line:95%,end
Right.

00:24:57.596 --> 00:24:58.797 line:95%,end
- None of it.
- MELISSA: That's fine.

00:24:58.864 --> 00:25:00.565 line:95%,end
If you don't want to be my
friend anymore-- because I

00:25:00.632 --> 00:25:02.200 line:95%,end
would do anything for your
kid kids, and you know it.

00:25:02.267 --> 00:25:03.969 line:95%,end
And I would do
anything for your kids.

00:25:04.035 --> 00:25:05.704 line:95%,end
Not any more, you
won't I'm sure.

00:25:05.770 --> 00:25:07.205 line:95%,end
I feel really lost.

00:25:07.305 --> 00:25:10.041 line:95%,end
I'm torn between my friendships
with my friends

00:25:10.141 --> 00:25:12.010 line:95%,end
and my children's dance careers.

00:25:12.077 --> 00:25:14.946 line:95%,end
Clearly, the most important
thing in the world to you

00:25:15.013 --> 00:25:17.816 line:95%,end
is if your kids win at dance
over our friendship,

00:25:17.916 --> 00:25:19.451 line:95%,end
over their friendships
with the kids.

00:25:19.518 --> 00:25:22.153 line:95%,end
You've made that quite clear,
not in your words,

00:25:22.220 --> 00:25:23.655 line:95%,end
but by your actions.

00:25:23.722 --> 00:25:25.824 line:95%,end
And you have denied it for three
years sitting here saying,

00:25:25.924 --> 00:25:27.692 line:95%,end
I don't care if my kids win.

00:25:27.792 --> 00:25:29.494 line:95%,end
So just sit here and own it.

00:25:29.561 --> 00:25:30.595 line:95%,end
Say, you know what?

00:25:30.662 --> 00:25:33.665 line:95%,end
I will do anything I need to
do-- don't sit here and act

00:25:33.765 --> 00:25:35.233 line:95%,end
like you're not a stage mom.

00:25:38.003 --> 00:25:39.938 line:95%,end
ABBY LEE: Foot underneath you.
Foot underneath you.

00:25:40.906 --> 00:25:42.274 line:95%,end
JILL: What's going on in there?

00:25:42.974 --> 00:25:44.509 line:95%,end
- What is going on in there?
- I don't know.

00:25:44.576 --> 00:25:47.879 line:95%,end
I thought we were having a
lesson, not a private
conversation.

00:25:48.547 --> 00:25:49.814 line:95%,end
Okay.

00:25:49.881 --> 00:25:52.183 line:95%,end
Dr. Holly might have
a PhD in education,

00:25:52.284 --> 00:25:54.753 line:95%,end
but Melissa has a PhD
in kissing Abby's ass.

00:25:55.720 --> 00:25:57.822 line:95%,end
[music playing]


00:26:01.493 --> 00:26:03.194 line:5%,start
